  "user_side_comments": {
    "1025": "10 REM LODE RUNNER ON COMMODORE PET",
    "1060": "20 REM JIM.ORLANDO@GMAIL.COM",
    "1088": "30 REM TESTED ON 3032,4032,8032",
    "1119": "40 PRINT CHR$(142):PRINT CHR$(147)",
    "1141": "50 PRINT CHR$(42)",
    "1153": "60 SYS 1536",
    "2742": "Self-modifying screen RAM target address (high byte).\nPaired with a0AB7 (low byte) to form a 16-bit address patched\ninto absolute STA instructions in draw_playfield_border and\nanimate_level_select_cursor, directing cursor-box writes to\nthe correct screen RAM location.\nInitial value $81 (hi) + $DF (lo) = $81DF.\nReset to $83 (hi) + $BF (lo) = $83BF after blit table setup.",
    "2743": "Self-modifying screen RAM target address (low byte). See a0AB6.",
    "2744": "Phase 1: draw border frame (25 rows x 33 cols) to screen RAM at $8000.",
    "3282": "",
